-- Shares of Brazil's state-run firms soar on election outlook
-- By Asher Levine
-- Mon Oct 13, 2014 01:51PM EDT
-- None



SAO PAULO, Oct 13 (Reuters) - Shares of Brazilian state-run companies skyrocketed on Monday as investors saw a higher likelihood of challenger Aecio Neves defeating President Dilma Rousseff in this month's election. [ID:nL2N0S80QE]

Preferred shares of Petroleo Brasileiro SA <PETR4.SA>, the oil producer known as Petrobras, soared about 11.5 percent and were on track to close with their biggest one-day gain in nearly six years. Shares of lender Banco do Brasil SA <BBAS3.SA> jumped almost 11 percent.